{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17413047","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17413047"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T07:52:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T07:52:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"341"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487401","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487401"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:09:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:09:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"341"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261100"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:52:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T10:28:52+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":62,"questionsAnswered":61,"marksTotal":61,"marksAttainable":61,"marksAttempted":61,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T09:15:31+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.2,"questionsCorrect":12,"marksCorrect":12},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"341","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/341"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.2,0.26,0.36,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"341"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"56036"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"341","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/341"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"341"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41587"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"343"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5475"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19082"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"56036","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/56036"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old man presents to his general practitioner with a tender wound six days after an open appendicectomy for perforated acute appendicitis. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination his blood pressure is 118/62 mmHg, pulse 90/min and temperature of 38.2\u00b0C. The only abnormality to find is a tender, reddened and fluctuant 4 cm diameter swelling at the medial end of the wound.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate first step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["White cell count and blood cultures","Ultrasound scan of wound and anterior abdominal wall","Broad spectrum antibiotics","Open the wound","CT abdomen"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient likely has a superficial wound infection - this is the most realistic explanation for his fever and the changes to his wound. All that is needed in the first instances is to gently \u003Cstrong\u003Eopen the wound\u003C/strong\u003E edges over the fluctuant area and the immediate release of pus will most likely resolve the issue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst a \u003Cstrong\u003Ewhite cell count \u003C/strong\u003Emight show a leucocytosis, it is not going to influence any decision-making with the need to open the wound and drain the collection. A tender, reddened and fluctuant swelling equates with a collection of pus and in such cases of a superficial collection, imaging studies (either \u003Cstrong\u003Eultrasound\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003ECT abdomen\u003C/strong\u003E) would be of very limited value and would not affect the management plan. Obviously if the patient was thought to be septic due to a more deep-seated collection (eg pelvic abscess), then some form of imaging would be appropriate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst it is quite possible that this patient will be given \u003Cstrong\u003Eantibiotics,\u003C/strong\u003E such management should follow on from initial drainage of the wound. More clear indications for the administration of antibiotics would be if the patient was septic or had co-morbidities (eg immunosuppression, prosthetic heart valve) that would put them at great risk should infection take hold.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Superficial and localised purulent post-operative infections can usually be treated by simple drainage alone."],"references":["Negut I, Grumezescu V, Grumezescu AM. Treatment Strategies for Infected Wounds. Molecules 2018; 23:2392. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6225154/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41587"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"341"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41587","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/41587"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-19T09:19:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-19T09:20:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"341"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"56036"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attribute